The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The local parameters header_name and header_value are declared as char * but are only used as read-only buffers (they are passed to MHD_add_response_entry_no_alloc_, asserted, and possibly freed; their contents are never modified in transmit_error_response_len). According to MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 these pointers should be const-qualified (const char *) when possible to document immutability and prevent accidental modification. Thus the current usage violates Rule 8.13 unless MHD_add_response_entry_no_alloc_ legitimately requires non-const (i.e. modifies those buffers); if that callee does not modify them, the pointers should be const.
